07933 |ref=harv}}\n\n{{refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin|2|indent=yes}}\n\n* Beck, Sanderson. ''India & Southeast Asia to 1800'' (2006)   [http://www.san.beck.org/2-10-Marathas1707-1800.html \"Marathas and the English Company 1701\u20131818\" online]. Retrieved 1 October 2004.\n* Kumar, Ravinder. ''Western India in the nineteenth century'' (Routledge, 2013).\n* Laine, James W. ''Shivaji: Hindu King in Islamic India'' (New York, 2003).\n* {{Citation|title=Pindari Society and the Establishment of British Paramountcy in India|location=Madison|oclc=53790277|first=Philip F|last=McEldowney|year=1966|publisher=University of Wisconsin|url=http://www.lib.virginia.edu/area-studies/SouthAsia/Ideas/pindaris.html}}\n* Moon, Penderel. ''The British Conquest and Dominion of India: Part One 1745-1857'' (1989).\n* {{cite journal|last1=Roy|first1=Tirthankar|title=Rethinking the Origins of British India: State Formation and Military-fiscal Undertakings in an Eighteenth Century World Region|journal=Modern Asian Studies|volume=47|issue=4|year=2013|pages=1125\u20131156|issn=0026-749X|doi=10.1017/S0026749X11000825|url=http://eprints.lse.ac.uk/28443/}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Sardesai|first=Govind Sakharam |title=New History of the Marathas: Shivaji and his line (1600-1707)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vXEfAAAAIAAJ|volume=Volume 1|year=1957|publisher=Phoenix Publications}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Seshan|first1=Radhika|title=The Maratha State|journal=Indian Historical Review|volume=41|issue=1|year=2014|pages=35\u201346|issn=0376-9836|doi=10.1177/0376983614521732}}\n* Wink, Andre. ''Land and Sovereignty in India: Agrarian Society and Politics under the Eighteenth Century Maratha Swarajya,'' (Cambridge UP, 1986).\n* [[Bombay University]] \u2013 ''Maratha History \u2013 Seminar Volume''\n* Samant, S. D. \u2013 ''Vedh Mahamanavacha''\n* Kasar, D.B. \u2013 ''Rigveda to Raigarh making of Shivaji the great'', Mumbai: Manudevi Prakashan (2005)\n* Apte, B.K. (editor) \u2013